        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48793",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmandaric",
                        "name": "dmandaric",
                        "displayName": "Djordje Mandaric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The issue can be circumvented by overriding the constant by passing in an array of options before making getDevice() call. \r\n\r\nE.g:\r\n\r\n$bootstrap = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance()->getParam('bootstrap');\r\n$userAgent = $bootstrap->getResource('useragent');\r\n\r\n$userAgent->setOptions(\r\n    array(\r\n        'storage' => array(\r\n            'adapter' => 'Zend_Http_UserAgent_Storage_Session'\r\n        )\r\n    )\r\n);",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmandaric",
                        "name": "dmandaric",
                        "displayName": "Djordje Mandaric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-26T00:51:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-26T00:51:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48794",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmandaric",
                        "name": "dmandaric",
                        "displayName": "Djordje Mandaric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am unable to find how to attach the following diff:\r\n\r\n--- src\/library\/Zend\/Http\/UserAgent.php\r\n+++ src\/library\/Zend\/Http\/UserAgent.php\r\n@@ -44,7 +44,7 @@\r\n     \/**\r\n      * Default persitent storage adapter : Session or NonPersitent\r\n      *\/\r\n-    const DEFAULT_PERSISTENT_STORAGE_ADAPTER = 'Session';\r\n+    const DEFAULT_PERSISTENT_STORAGE_ADAPTER = 'Zend_Http_UserAgent_Storage_Session';\r\n\r\n     \/**\r\n      * 'desktop' by default if the sequence return false for each item\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmandaric",
                        "name": "dmandaric",
                        "displayName": "Djordje Mandaric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-26T00:54:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-26T00:54:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48817",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can only attach patches to tickets if you've signed a Zend Framework developer CLA.\r\n\r\nAs for your problem, could you provide code to show how you are using {{Zend_Http_UserAgent}}?  Specifically, where is the error being raised from:\r\n{code}\r\nFatal error: Uncaught exception 'ExceptionInvalidSession' with message 'We didn't recognize either your\r\nusername or password. Try again.'\r\n{code}\r\nAFAIK, that isn't something that Zend Framework would raise\/throw.\r\n\r\nThe default value for {{DEFAULT_PERSISTENT_STORAGE_ADAPTER}} is correct, as internally {{Zend_Http_UserAgent}} uses a plugin broker to automatically locate the storage adapter based upon that short name (ie: plugin broker prepends 'Zend_Http_UserAgent_Storage_' to that value to get the full class name and then attempts to autoload the class (from Zend\/Http\/UserAgent\/Storage\/Session.php))\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-27T18:25:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-27T18:25:56.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
